{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"broken-checkered-tiger","description":"## Why\nThe agent landing contract only works if agents adopt it: the old \"watch the 2 votes\" model is now broken (two green votes no longer means \"it will land\" — a conflict blocks it while votes stay green). Docs must teach the new contract or the conflict case silently reintroduces babysitting.\n## What\nRewrite this repo's landing section in `CLAUDE.md` + `CONTRIBUTING.md` to the new contract, and record the design in `docs/adr/0042-*.md`.\n## Scope\nDocs + ADR only.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` + `CONTRIBUTING.md` landing section rewritten: \"set `Autosubmit` / run `land`; act on the single typed outcome; do NOT watch votes or treat two green votes as 'it will land'.\"\n- [ ] `docs/adr/0042-*.md` records the auto-lander, the agent contract + outcome enum, the staged serial→batch plan, and the separation-of-concerns boundary (project infra, not `rebar` core; provider-seam deferred to idea 1701-8bc1-e3b7-4984).\n- [ ] Docs cross-reference ADR-0040 (FFO) + ADR-0041 (LLM-Review `TRIVIAL_REBASE` carry) as the gate substrate the lander sits on.","id":"b825-a233-97d4-45c2","parent_id":"f1fa-57d8-07cb-44af","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"S6 Docs (CLAUDE.md/CONTRIBUTING.md landing-contract rewrite) + ADR-0042"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783721696493374001,"uuid":"228af34f-be4d-4245-a982-fef8e0480017"}